# Development Guide

## Build / test / lint commands

```bash
make build              # vendor + fmt + vet, outputs bin/hypershift-addon
make test               # Unit tests (envtest, all packages except e2e)
make test-no-cover      # Same without coverage
make fmt                # go fmt ./...
make vet                # go vet ./...
make vendor             # go mod tidy + go mod vendor
make docker-build       # Build container image
make build-e2e          # Compile e2e test binary
```

### Running a single test

```bash
go test ./pkg/manager/ -run TestSpecificName -v
go test ./pkg/agent/ -run TestSpecificName -v -timeout 300s
go test ./pkg/install/ -run TestSpecificName -v -timeout 300s
```

## Dependencies

Dependencies are vendored. After changing `go.mod`, always run `make vendor`. The `make build` target runs `go mod tidy` and `go mod vendor` automatically.

Key dependency: `github.com/openshift/hypershift/api` transitively pulls in `sigs.k8s.io/karpenter` which constrains the minimum Go version.

## CI systems

- **Prow:** OpenShift CI for release branches (config in `openshift/release` repo). Tests: `unit`, `sonar`, `pr-image-mirror`.
- **Konflux/Tekton:** RHTAP pipeline for productization builds (`.tekton/`)
- **SonarQube:** Code quality gate requires ≥70% coverage on new code

## Release branches

Release branches follow `backplane-X.YY` (e.g., `backplane-2.11`). The main development branch is `main`. Cherry-picks use `/cherry-pick backplane-X.YY` Prow command.

## Dockerfile variants

- `Dockerfile` — CI build using `registry.ci.openshift.org/stolostron/builder:go1.26-linux`
- `Dockerfile.rhtap` — Red Hat productization build using `brew.registry.redhat.io/rh-osbs/openshift-golang-builder`
- `Dockerfile.canary` — Canary test image

## Testing on a live cluster

1. Build for amd64: `docker buildx build --platform linux/amd64 -t quay.io/<user>/hypershift-addon-operator:<tag> --push -f Dockerfile .`
2. Scale down MCE operator: `oc scale deployment multicluster-engine-operator -n multicluster-engine --replicas=0`
3. Patch manager image: `oc set image deployment/hypershift-addon-manager -n multicluster-engine hypershift-addon-manager=<image>`
4. Patch agent image env: `oc set env deployment/hypershift-addon-manager -n multicluster-engine HYPERSHIFT_ADDON_IMAGE_NAME=<image>`
5. Scale MCE operator back up when done

